Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1650
H.P. 1091 House of Representatives, April 15, 2025
Public Defense Services
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative COLLINS of Sidney.
Cosponsored by Representatives: BOYER of Poland, DRINKWATER of Milford, HAGGAN
of Hampden, SOBOLESKI of Phillips, Senator: HAGGAN of Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 4 MRSA §1804, sub-§3, ¶F-1 is enacted to read:
3 F-1. Develop and maintain a system to compensate paralegals employed to assist in
4 providing indigent legal services at the average labor market rate for paralegal services;
5 SUMMARY
66 This bill requires the Maine Commission on Public Defense Services to implement a
77 system to compensate paralegals employed to help provide indigent legal services at the
88 average labor market rate for paralegal services.
